03:13.062 --> 03:17.458
♪ I'm about to kick your ass
Through the door ♪

03:17.501 --> 03:19.460
♪ Carry me further in regret

03:19.503 --> 03:20.025
♪ I tried to leave but regret's
Got quite the death grip ♪

03:23.115 --> 03:24.682
[knocks on door]

03:37.826 --> 03:40.307
-[clears throat] Come in!

03:50.142 --> 03:51.579
-[clears throat]

03:51.622 --> 03:53.581
-Please, I beg of you.

03:53.624 --> 03:57.149
Do not do Marilyn Monroe singing
"Happy Birthday" to JFK.

03:57.193 --> 03:58.673
I'll die.

03:58.716 --> 04:00.631
-Okay, but
I'm only sparing you

04:00.675 --> 04:03.025
because it's your birthday.

04:03.068 --> 04:04.635
-Thank you.

04:04.679 --> 04:07.638
-That's "Thank you,
Mister President,"

04:07.682 --> 04:10.380
to you.
-No!

04:10.424 --> 04:13.122
-At least you had the decency
to pretend to be asleep.

04:13.165 --> 04:15.080
-What do you mean?

04:15.124 --> 04:16.691
-Don't play innocent.
You can't lie to me.

04:16.734 --> 04:18.867
Now, make a wish,
and don't tell me what it is,

04:18.910 --> 04:19.911
no matter what
I threaten you with.

04:24.916 --> 04:26.266
[Polaroid snaps,
developing picture]

04:27.528 --> 04:28.746
-Hot.

04:30.574 --> 04:31.488
-Cute.

04:34.186 --> 04:35.884
Ugh!

04:35.927 --> 04:38.713
Please tell me
you'll throw that out.

04:38.756 --> 04:41.411
-I will if you tell me
what you wished for.

04:41.455 --> 04:42.891
-You told me not to.

04:42.934 --> 04:45.850
-Hm. Then look where
it's going...

04:45.894 --> 04:48.984
into my bag to show
all my friends.

04:49.027 --> 04:50.333
-Yeah, well, luckily,

04:50.377 --> 04:52.727
I know you don't have any
besides me.

04:52.770 --> 04:55.730
-Um, what do you think
you're doing, young lady?

04:55.773 --> 04:57.558
-Eating breakfast
before dessert,

04:57.601 --> 04:59.429
like a normal human being.

04:59.473 --> 05:01.823
-That is a violation of
at least three birthday laws.

05:01.866 --> 05:05.566
I insist that you eat every last
crumb of your birthday cake,

05:05.609 --> 05:08.220
and then let me make you
some of that disgusting

05:08.264 --> 05:10.962
vegetarian bacon
you claim is edible.

05:13.878 --> 05:15.358
-I'll tell you
what I wished for.

05:15.402 --> 05:16.533
-Deal.

05:19.841 --> 05:22.713
Honey, you're doing that thing.
What's up?

05:22.757 --> 05:27.805
-Uh, nothing.
Yeah. It's stupid.

05:27.849 --> 05:32.332
-Nothing you want is stupid.
Tell me.

05:32.375 --> 05:35.596
-[chuckles]
I've been thinking about

05:35.639 --> 05:39.164
changing my last name to Jones.
Officially.

05:41.079 --> 05:46.346
-Uh, yeah. Listen.

05:46.389 --> 05:48.826
You can change your name
if you want.

05:48.870 --> 05:52.308
But there's a reason
I gave you his.

05:52.352 --> 05:54.963
-To guarantee
I never date until my 40s?

05:55.006 --> 05:56.312
-To make sure
that neither of us forgets.

05:58.445 --> 06:01.230
I mean, no matter what
the paperwork says...

06:01.273 --> 06:04.364
Believe me.
I have been trying for years,

06:04.407 --> 06:06.278
and you can't erase him
that easily.

06:06.322 --> 06:08.019
He doesn't just go away.

06:10.021 --> 06:11.936
And it's...

06:11.980 --> 06:13.590
safer not to pretend
that he has.

06:18.421 --> 06:19.640
Anything else
you want to tell me?

06:20.989 --> 06:22.730
-Mm, no.

06:25.080 --> 06:26.298
-This came yesterday...

06:30.825 --> 06:33.044
It's a great school.

06:33.088 --> 06:34.916
And I know you've been checking
online every five minutes.

06:34.959 --> 06:38.528
I don't understand
why you didn't tell me.

06:38.572 --> 06:41.879
-It's on the East Coast.

06:41.923 --> 06:43.664
-We'll make it work.

06:43.707 --> 06:45.143
I can always get an apartment
near campus.

06:48.146 --> 06:50.279
I am kidding.

06:50.322 --> 06:52.063
Now go get your bathing suit on.

06:52.107 --> 06:54.762
-Mom. I have school.

06:54.805 --> 06:58.374
-Uh, birthday statute 435.

06:58.418 --> 07:01.116
"Thou shalt not attendeth school
on thy birthday."

07:01.159 --> 07:02.465
-Where's the rule against

07:02.509 --> 07:04.206
bossing around
the birthday girl?

07:04.249 --> 07:07.078
[unsettling music playing]

07:10.430 --> 07:12.170
-[giggling]

07:12.214 --> 07:14.172
-That one guy's bathing suit

07:14.216 --> 07:15.696
should have counted
as a sex crime.

07:16.958 --> 07:19.613
-There is no excuse
to wear a Speedo

07:19.656 --> 07:20.875
in the 21st century.

07:20.918 --> 07:22.267
-No, you can't--

07:22.311 --> 07:23.747
you can't have
a Speedo and a mustache.

07:23.791 --> 07:25.575
One is the legal limit.

07:25.619 --> 07:27.795
[chuckling]

07:27.838 --> 07:29.797
-Hey, wait, where do you
think you're going, missy?

07:29.840 --> 07:31.668
-To bed.

07:31.712 --> 07:33.496
-But it's still
your birthday for...

07:33.540 --> 07:35.063
39 more minutes.

07:35.106 --> 07:37.195
I'll--I'll brew us a pot
of extra strong coffee,

07:37.239 --> 07:39.502
we can stay up late,
watch a scary movie,

07:39.546 --> 07:41.243
eat candy until we feel sick?

07:41.286 --> 07:43.680
-Mom, I already feel sick
from eating cake for breakfast

07:43.724 --> 07:45.813
and three veggie dogs for lunch.

07:45.856 --> 07:47.249
-Until we feel more sick?

07:47.292 --> 07:49.730
-I have school
in the morning, okay?

07:49.773 --> 07:51.514
I don't want to be tired.
And don't you have to work?

07:51.558 --> 07:53.560
-I actually sell more houses

07:53.603 --> 07:55.953
when I'm half asleep.
It makes me a better liar.

07:55.997 --> 07:57.781
-I'm gonna go to bed,
all right?

07:57.825 --> 07:59.870
You--I'll close my door
so you can watch

07:59.914 --> 08:01.611
whatever you want
by yourself.

08:03.308 --> 08:04.745
Good night, Mom!

08:07.661 --> 08:08.531
[door slams]

08:11.708 --> 08:14.537
[emotional music playing]

08:32.903 --> 08:35.732
[door opening slowly]

08:41.782 --> 08:44.567
[creature breathing
through mask]

08:58.320 --> 08:59.495
-[gasping]

09:03.934 --> 09:05.370
[panting for breath]

09:19.210 --> 09:21.038
-[Sunny crying faintly]

09:30.526 --> 09:32.397
[still crying]

09:36.053 --> 09:37.141
-Mom?

09:39.535 --> 09:40.623
Are you okay?

09:44.888 --> 09:48.152
-This came for me today.
Without a stamp.

09:51.852 --> 09:55.377
-"She has been prioritizing
the plush monkey all her life.

09:55.420 --> 09:57.945
"I will teach her
to choose wire.

09:57.988 --> 10:01.513
It's time.
I am coming for her."

10:01.557 --> 10:02.993
I don't get it.

10:05.213 --> 10:06.562
-It's from him.

10:15.702 --> 10:16.790
-How?

10:20.054 --> 10:21.446
"I'm coming for her?"

10:23.710 --> 10:26.930
-You. He means you.

10:32.109 --> 10:34.982
-Okay. Um...
we'll call the police.

10:35.025 --> 10:36.505
It'll be fine.
-No. No, you don't know him.

10:38.028 --> 10:39.856
The cops won't do any good.
They'll make things worse.

10:39.900 --> 10:40.988
-Well then, what?

10:50.693 --> 10:51.738
-Pack a bag.

10:53.957 --> 10:55.785
I know a place we can go.

10:58.440 --> 10:59.528
[paper crumples]

11:07.275 --> 11:08.102
[approaching footsteps]

11:09.799 --> 11:12.802
KARMA: Please don't tell me
you forgot to renew triple A.

11:12.846 --> 11:15.283
-I don't want to talk about it.

11:15.326 --> 11:16.806
-Why'd you even open it?

11:16.850 --> 11:18.547
-I don't know.

11:18.590 --> 11:21.985
Better to do something
than nothing.

11:22.029 --> 11:23.944
-Can we get an Uber there?

11:23.987 --> 11:25.380
-Nah, it's too far.

11:26.773 --> 11:28.078
[hood closes]

11:28.122 --> 11:29.601
We could hitchhike.

11:29.645 --> 11:31.081
-Mom!

11:31.125 --> 11:32.735
That's like a guaranteed way
to get murdered.

11:32.779 --> 11:34.171
Absolutely not.

11:34.215 --> 11:36.260
-Your generation is so fragile.

11:37.522 --> 11:39.350
-Maybe yours wasn't
fragile enough.

11:44.573 --> 11:45.705
[car door opens]

11:49.230 --> 11:51.014
-[trunk closes]
-[car engine starts]

11:52.363 --> 11:53.887
-Hey! Quick! Get in.

11:56.454 --> 11:58.282
-Don't you think
you should maybe, like,

11:58.326 --> 12:00.981
I don't know,
tell me some stuff?

12:01.024 --> 12:02.939
-Stuff?

12:02.983 --> 12:05.812
-You know what I mean.

12:05.855 --> 12:09.250
-Honestly, I don't.

12:09.293 --> 12:10.686
-About him.

12:15.386 --> 12:17.432
-I've seen your search history.

12:17.475 --> 12:20.565
You've seen every article
ever written about him.

12:20.609 --> 12:22.959
What more do you want to know?

12:23.003 --> 12:24.831
-What happened to you.

12:24.874 --> 12:26.310
-No.
-KARMA: No?

12:27.921 --> 12:29.270
That's it?

12:29.313 --> 12:30.750
Mom.

12:30.793 --> 12:32.012
It feels like
I'm going in blind here

12:32.055 --> 12:33.143
and it might help to actually,

12:33.187 --> 12:33.883
like, know--
-It won't.

12:36.886 --> 12:38.583
What you don't know

12:38.627 --> 12:41.586
is the only thing keeping you
calm and sane right now,

12:41.630 --> 12:43.066
I promise.

13:00.780 --> 13:03.260
[car engine revving]

13:12.008 --> 13:14.837
[foreboding music playing]

13:55.922 --> 13:57.619
[gears shift]

13:57.662 --> 13:59.490
-Sunny.
-SUNNY: Hi.

13:59.534 --> 14:01.753
BUTCH: Hey, look at you, huh?

14:01.797 --> 14:03.886
[car doors closing]

14:03.930 --> 14:05.888
And that must be Karma.

14:05.932 --> 14:08.412
-Hmm. Yeah.

14:08.456 --> 14:10.850
-Oh, yeah. Hugs.

14:11.938 --> 14:14.854
-Karma, this is Butch.

14:14.897 --> 14:16.594
I'd really hate to see
how you say hello

14:16.638 --> 14:18.248
to someone you don't like.

14:18.292 --> 14:20.163
-Ah, yeah.
Sorry about that.

14:20.207 --> 14:21.425
Didn't--didn't mean to
give you a start.

14:21.469 --> 14:23.079
But, you know,

14:23.123 --> 14:25.038
you can't be too careful, right?

14:25.081 --> 14:26.430
-SUNNY: Hm.
-Especially now.

14:27.692 --> 14:29.477
So, uh, why don't we go inside

14:29.520 --> 14:31.479
and let Priscilla
feed you some breakfast?

14:31.522 --> 14:32.741
That'll make her happy.

14:34.525 --> 14:35.613
I'll get the gate.

14:41.706 --> 14:43.752
-Did you see something...?

14:43.795 --> 14:46.798
-What? No.
I'm sure it was just the wind.

14:46.842 --> 14:48.278
Or that big head of yours

14:48.322 --> 14:49.714
making up stuff
like it sometimes does.

14:49.758 --> 14:50.846
-[scoffs]

14:53.849 --> 14:57.113
-Sorry, little lady. We prefer
to stay off the grid here.

14:57.157 --> 15:00.073
You know those things
are homing beacons, right?

15:00.116 --> 15:02.466
Lead somebody right to you.

15:02.510 --> 15:03.598
-He's right.

15:03.641 --> 15:06.166
-So you guys don't have Wi-Fi?

15:06.209 --> 15:07.471
-Not even dial-up.

15:09.430 --> 15:12.215
So, come on.
Let's eat. After you.

15:24.140 --> 15:25.794
After you.

15:25.837 --> 15:26.969
-Hi.

15:28.971 --> 15:31.408
-Ah, Karma,
this is my wife, Priscilla.

15:31.452 --> 15:32.540
[door closes]

15:32.583 --> 15:33.976
And you remember Sunny.

15:35.282 --> 15:37.980
Well, sit, sit.
We're not formal here.

15:42.158 --> 15:45.509
Mm, hope you like
your bacon crisp.

15:45.553 --> 15:48.295
I prefer mine chewy,
but I'm happy to defer

15:48.338 --> 15:50.558
to the majority
on special occasions.

15:54.997 --> 15:56.564
Karma, are you a vegetarian?

15:56.607 --> 15:58.827
-Vegan. Sorry,
we should have told you.

15:58.870 --> 16:00.220
-No, no. Nonsense.

16:00.263 --> 16:01.612
We'll keep that
warm in the oven

16:01.656 --> 16:04.050
and Priscilla will whip you up

16:04.093 --> 16:06.966
one of her delicious
soy protein shakes.

16:07.009 --> 16:08.445
-No, no,
I--I'm not even hungry.

16:08.489 --> 16:11.013
-No, it's no trouble. Really.

16:11.057 --> 16:12.710
I'll get some strawberries
from the garden.

16:12.754 --> 16:13.929
She'll like those.

16:13.973 --> 16:15.322
-[door opens, closes]
-Hm.

16:16.888 --> 16:18.716
-Does she not talk?

16:18.760 --> 16:21.154
-Hasn't in years.

16:21.197 --> 16:23.243
-What happened to her?

16:23.286 --> 16:26.202
-Sometimes when you stay
quiet for too long, it sticks.

16:26.246 --> 16:28.248
[distant glass shatters]

16:28.291 --> 16:29.771
I'm going to go
check on that shake.

16:33.209 --> 16:34.994
[footsteps receding,
floorboard creaking]

16:36.473 --> 16:40.390
Hey, Priscilla,
let me help you with that.

16:40.434 --> 16:46.048
[distant blender whirring]

16:46.092 --> 16:48.181
[tense burst of music]

16:48.224 --> 16:49.617
[distant creaking]

16:53.273 --> 16:54.361
[distant blender whirring]

16:54.404 --> 16:55.275
[door shuts]

16:56.841 --> 16:59.061
[tense music continues]

16:59.105 --> 17:02.934
Sorry. That was a whole drama
with Butch and the garden.

17:02.978 --> 17:04.632
You would not believe
how much dirt goes into

17:04.675 --> 17:07.069
this whole
fruit and vegetable thing.

17:07.113 --> 17:09.332
Make sure you finish
the whole thing.

17:09.376 --> 17:10.899
Breakfast is the most important
meal of the day,

17:10.942 --> 17:13.119
or at least
that's what they say.

17:13.162 --> 17:14.772
-It tastes weird.

17:14.816 --> 17:16.078
[footsteps]

17:16.122 --> 17:17.949
-So, how's the shake?

17:17.993 --> 17:20.126
-Delicious.

17:20.169 --> 17:22.389
-I told you. [chuckles]

17:22.432 --> 17:23.999
Sunny,
you'll have the works, right?

17:24.043 --> 17:25.696
-Yes, please.
-BUTCH: There you go.

17:28.308 --> 17:33.008
So, Karma, your mom tells me

17:33.052 --> 17:36.490
that you got into
some really fine schools.

17:39.058 --> 17:41.495
You must be very excited
about next year.

17:41.538 --> 17:43.410
[slams her glass]

17:43.453 --> 17:45.151
-I'm sorry,
but can we talk about

17:45.194 --> 17:47.240
what's actually going on here
for a minute?

17:47.283 --> 17:49.851
-Karma. Don't be rude.

17:49.894 --> 17:52.680
-No. It's...
it's quite all right.

17:52.723 --> 17:54.464
But nothing's going on.

17:54.508 --> 17:56.379
You're safe here.

17:56.423 --> 17:59.034
That fence outside?
It's impenetrable.

17:59.078 --> 18:02.124
The gate we have chained
and padlocked.

18:02.168 --> 18:04.692
There are motion sensors
all around the edges,

18:04.735 --> 18:08.217
so we're gonna know if anybody
gets too close for comfort.

18:08.261 --> 18:13.396
The only way anybody gets in
is if I let them in.

18:13.440 --> 18:17.096
And that's not going to happen.

18:17.139 --> 18:18.532
-I just wish you guys
would stop acting

18:18.575 --> 18:19.924
like everything's okay.

18:24.103 --> 18:26.017
-Old habits die hard, I guess.

18:28.542 --> 18:31.980
-I'm not feeling very well.
May I please be excused?

18:32.023 --> 18:33.547
-Of course. You want to lie down
in our room,

18:33.590 --> 18:34.983
you're more than welcome to.

18:35.026 --> 18:37.203
-No, that's okay.
[clears throat]

18:37.246 --> 18:40.249
[door opens, closes]

18:45.776 --> 18:48.562
[soft unsettling music playing]

18:56.874 --> 18:57.962
[phone thuds]

19:08.408 --> 19:09.583
-Thank you, darling.

19:13.108 --> 19:15.110
-Was it true
what you said to her?

19:15.154 --> 19:17.504
About how safe it is here?

19:17.547 --> 19:19.201
-Yeah.

19:19.245 --> 19:22.335
There are no cell phone towers,
no data, no cloud.

19:22.378 --> 19:23.988
[water running on dishes]

19:24.032 --> 19:26.730
No one out there
even knows we're here.

19:26.774 --> 19:28.471
SUNNY: And Paul?

19:28.515 --> 19:30.821
Where is he?

19:30.865 --> 19:32.736
-Well, the authorities
were last tracking him

19:32.780 --> 19:34.434
in Oaxaca, Mexico.

19:36.784 --> 19:39.830
-But somebody dropped
that note at our place.

19:39.874 --> 19:42.093
-He could've paid
anybody to do that.

19:42.137 --> 19:43.791
Not necessarily a believer.

19:43.834 --> 19:46.359
[water running]

19:46.402 --> 19:49.362
-How many do you think
he still has?

19:49.405 --> 19:50.232
-[faint creaking]
-BUTCH: Well, Wendell's never

19:50.276 --> 19:51.842
left his side.

19:51.886 --> 19:54.976
A big, quiet man always
shows up in the reports.

19:55.019 --> 19:56.717
I don't need to tell you--

19:56.760 --> 20:00.199
I mean, Paul is basically
the Pied Piper of lost souls.

20:00.242 --> 20:02.636
He can get anyone
to follow him through fire

20:02.679 --> 20:05.116
and not ask for water
on the other side.

20:05.160 --> 20:06.205
-[chuckles]

20:10.557 --> 20:11.993
But that far in in Mexico.

20:12.036 --> 20:14.213
I thought he was
sticking closer to TJ.

20:16.432 --> 20:19.087
-Well, a few too many girls
disappeared.

20:19.130 --> 20:20.784
He had to move on.

20:20.828 --> 20:22.482
-Yeah.

20:22.525 --> 20:25.920
In some ways, I'm sure Mexico
is perfect for him.

20:25.963 --> 20:27.791
Remember when all those
factory women turned up missing

20:27.835 --> 20:28.705
a few years back?

20:30.141 --> 20:31.447
-Yeah.

20:31.491 --> 20:34.755
Well, as long as
you're poor and brown,

20:34.798 --> 20:37.627
no one seems to care.

20:37.671 --> 20:38.933
-[breathes deeply]

20:44.199 --> 20:45.505
[knife thuds]

20:52.990 --> 20:53.948
[door closes]

21:02.348 --> 21:05.525
-I'm sorry if I scared you
last night.

21:05.568 --> 21:08.615
That's part of why I don't like
talking about your father.

21:08.658 --> 21:10.660
I don't want to give you fear
that isn't yours.

21:10.704 --> 21:14.838
-It's okay. I just wish you
wouldn't treat me like a child.

21:14.882 --> 21:17.667
-Honey, you are a child.

21:17.711 --> 21:19.452
It's my job to treat you
like one.

21:19.495 --> 21:22.150
-I'm the same age now
as you were when you had me.

21:22.193 --> 21:24.239
-Believe me,
I was a child then, too.

21:29.026 --> 21:30.289
-Do you trust him?

21:30.332 --> 21:32.029
-Who?
-Butch.

21:32.073 --> 21:34.118
-Absolutely. With my life.

21:37.644 --> 21:39.254
-Mom, I think there was
something in that shake.

21:39.298 --> 21:41.082
I don't feel right.

21:41.125 --> 21:43.345
-No, I'm sure it's just nerves.

21:43.389 --> 21:45.216
Look, Butch went to
an awful lot of trouble

21:45.260 --> 21:46.957
to make sure he didn't
have to hurt people anymore.

21:47.001 --> 21:48.263
He's not going to
start again now.

21:49.525 --> 21:51.484
-That's comforting.

21:51.527 --> 21:53.312
-Maybe you should lie down,
like he said.

21:56.445 --> 21:57.751
Come.

22:02.451 --> 22:04.323
[strains]

22:04.366 --> 22:06.368
[teasing]
Tsk, tsk, tsk, tsk, tsk.

22:06.412 --> 22:07.587
Ssshhhh.

22:10.938 --> 22:13.723
I'll be right outside
if you need anything, okay?

22:22.906 --> 22:24.778
[footsteps receding]

22:26.562 --> 22:27.998
-[sighing]

22:30.131 --> 22:33.003
[♪♪♪]

22:58.768 --> 23:01.641
[♪♪♪]

23:16.960 --> 23:18.875
[clattering]

23:28.842 --> 23:30.931
[bottle thuds]

23:34.804 --> 23:35.892
[sighs]

23:53.997 --> 23:54.868
[box unlocks]

24:36.953 --> 24:39.478
-The scorpion fly
represents reincarnation.

24:41.915 --> 24:43.960
The larvae appear to die

24:44.004 --> 24:45.832
before they're reborn
as adult flies

24:45.875 --> 24:49.009
who then give birth
to new larvae,

24:49.052 --> 24:51.098
beginning the cycle
all over again.

24:51.141 --> 24:54.536
-I'm--I'm--I'm so sorry. I--
-BUTCH: You were scared.

24:54.580 --> 24:56.538
And wondering if I was
the embodiment of everything

24:56.582 --> 24:57.800
you are running from.

25:02.326 --> 25:04.720
I don't blame you.

25:04.764 --> 25:07.810
-What are these?
That--that mask, I--

25:07.854 --> 25:09.595
-They're reminders
of why I left.

25:12.598 --> 25:15.339
I keep these in case
I'm ever tempted to go back.

25:18.255 --> 25:23.217
This is our daughter, Cindy,
the night she died.

25:23.260 --> 25:24.523
-What happened?

25:25.741 --> 25:28.265
-A failed reincarnation.

25:30.093 --> 25:32.095
I'm surprised your mother
hasn't told you about them.

25:32.139 --> 25:33.706
-No. She won't tell me
any of it.

25:33.749 --> 25:37.579
It's like it never happened.

25:37.623 --> 25:40.103
Is that why you left?

25:40.147 --> 25:43.106
-Yeah. And why I sold out
every friend I had

25:43.150 --> 25:46.719
to try and send
your father to prison.

25:46.762 --> 25:48.590
Instead,
I loosed him on Mexico,

25:48.634 --> 25:50.244
and guaranteed
my wife and I would live

25:50.287 --> 25:52.594
running from our shadows
for the rest of our days.

25:55.902 --> 25:59.427
There is some beauty in it.

25:59.470 --> 26:04.563
The promise of a life
never ends.

26:04.606 --> 26:06.739
The end to the fear of death.

26:08.697 --> 26:11.004
And in my experience,

26:11.047 --> 26:16.313
the more we resist
the inevitable,

26:16.357 --> 26:17.663
the more we bring it on.

26:19.621 --> 26:21.405
-I need--I need some air.

26:21.449 --> 26:23.538
-Well, we got plenty of that.

26:23.582 --> 26:25.540
I'll go with you.
-No, no. I'd rather be alone.

26:25.584 --> 26:27.020
I'll--I'll be fine. Honestly.

26:36.551 --> 26:39.380
[soft music playing]

26:50.870 --> 26:53.742
[hyperventilating]

27:08.496 --> 27:10.063
[distant splatter]

27:10.106 --> 27:11.151
[intense burst of music]

27:14.894 --> 27:15.938
[breathing heavily] Hello?

27:17.505 --> 27:18.637
Is anyone in there?

27:22.249 --> 27:23.337
[screams]

27:25.078 --> 27:27.776
[breathing heavily]

27:27.820 --> 27:30.083
[alarm system bleating]

27:35.610 --> 27:36.567
Mom!

27:38.744 --> 27:41.703
[drawer opens, closes]

27:45.141 --> 27:46.882
-Priscilla?
Where are you?

27:48.667 --> 27:49.580
Priscilla!

27:51.626 --> 27:52.583
Priscilla!

27:55.325 --> 27:57.719
Darling, we got to go.

27:59.460 --> 28:00.635
All right?

28:00.679 --> 28:01.767
[keys jingle]

28:01.810 --> 28:03.725
I need you to go start the car.

28:03.769 --> 28:05.509
I'm going to go get weapons
from the shed

28:05.553 --> 28:08.469
and then find Karma and Sunny.

28:08.512 --> 28:12.255
Listen to me, it's going to be
all right, I promise.

28:12.299 --> 28:13.648
It's probably
just a squirrel again,

28:13.692 --> 28:18.566
but just in case,
I need you to move.

28:18.609 --> 28:20.437
Come on. Let's go.

28:20.481 --> 28:22.657
[alarm system continues
bleating]

28:22.701 --> 28:23.614
[door closes]

28:27.401 --> 28:29.272
[alarm system silenced]

28:29.316 --> 28:30.230
[gun fired]

28:34.103 --> 28:35.844
Wendell.
How the fuck did you get in?

28:37.019 --> 28:39.674
Hey. Take me.

28:39.718 --> 28:41.154
Just leave Priscilla.

28:41.197 --> 28:43.243
She doesn't know anything.
She never talked.

28:43.286 --> 28:45.332
She can't talk.

28:45.375 --> 28:48.727
Please. I'm the one you want.

28:48.770 --> 28:51.120
-You are a rat.

28:53.775 --> 28:58.649
Rats don't kneel. They run.

28:58.693 --> 29:00.564
Run.

29:00.608 --> 29:01.609
Run!

29:05.787 --> 29:09.922
-[door opens]
-[Sunny's muffled breathing]

29:09.965 --> 29:11.532
-Mom? Ah!

29:11.575 --> 29:12.620
-[muffled sobs]

29:14.578 --> 29:15.492
-[Karma shrieks]

29:20.367 --> 29:22.935
[breathing heavily]

29:22.978 --> 29:24.850
[mouse squeaking]

29:33.293 --> 29:34.816
[door knob rattles]

29:34.860 --> 29:37.036
-[bangs on door]
-Hello! Is anybody out there?

29:38.341 --> 29:40.082
-[door knob rattles]
-[mouse squeaking]

29:45.392 --> 29:46.828
-Hey.

29:46.872 --> 29:49.309
You can come out.

29:49.352 --> 29:50.963
I'm not going to hurt you,
I promise.

29:51.006 --> 29:52.486
[mouse squeaking]

29:52.529 --> 29:53.574
[distant creak]

29:56.882 --> 30:02.148
[gasps]

30:02.191 --> 30:03.584
[cries] Mom!

30:03.627 --> 30:05.804
[heart pounding]

30:17.119 --> 30:18.381
[gasping]

30:18.425 --> 30:20.296
[mouse squeaking]

30:27.347 --> 30:29.392
[cries]

30:31.003 --> 30:34.702
Stop, stop, stop,
stop, stop, stop,

30:34.745 --> 30:37.748
stop, stop, stop,
stop, stop, stop.

30:44.843 --> 30:48.063
-Oh. Don't tell me
you never made it to the car?

30:48.107 --> 30:50.936
Where are the keys?
Give me the keys.

30:50.979 --> 30:53.373
Oh, no, no, no, I'm sorry,
my love, I'm sorry.

30:53.416 --> 30:56.071
But I do need you to stand up.

30:56.115 --> 30:57.725
Now. Now.

31:01.381 --> 31:04.210
Listen to me.
It's going to be okay.

31:04.253 --> 31:07.822
It's going to be okay.
But we have to go. Let's go.

31:13.393 --> 31:16.265
[mouse squeaking]

31:22.532 --> 31:24.404
-[breathing heavily]

31:36.851 --> 31:37.896
PAUL: Hello, Karma.

31:40.289 --> 31:43.945
-I know you're not real.
You're not real.

31:52.998 --> 31:55.870
[tense beats of music]

31:59.613 --> 32:01.397
-You're a lot shorter
than I thought you'd be.

32:04.618 --> 32:07.969
But, uh, you know, you're...

32:10.058 --> 32:12.669
every bit as weak.

32:12.713 --> 32:15.411
That figures, you know,
considering how your mother is.

32:15.455 --> 32:18.806
-Fuck you.
Where--where is she?

32:18.849 --> 32:21.026
-There you go.
You're catching up.

32:21.069 --> 32:24.464
There you go...
uh, she's where she should be.

32:27.510 --> 32:30.731
-You're not real.
You're not real.

32:30.774 --> 32:31.993
-Oh, yes I am.

32:33.821 --> 32:36.650
You're seeing things, you see,

32:36.693 --> 32:41.002
because you're very,
very close to divinity.

32:42.264 --> 32:44.353
I'm curious:
Are you a virgin?

32:44.397 --> 32:47.226
-What? What...?

32:47.269 --> 32:48.575
-Do boys want to touch you?

32:48.618 --> 32:51.404
When even like probably not

32:51.447 --> 32:53.319
if they find out who
your father is, right?

32:53.362 --> 32:56.235
Maybe they get off on it.
[laughs]

32:56.278 --> 32:57.671
-That's disgusting.

32:59.455 --> 33:01.501
-I'm guessing virgin.

33:01.544 --> 33:04.721
I'm guessing
you're a virgin, yeah.

33:04.765 --> 33:07.072
You don't smell like a slut.
[sniffs]

33:09.204 --> 33:12.599
I can smell one of them
from across the room.

33:12.642 --> 33:14.470
-What do you want from me?

33:14.514 --> 33:16.298
Why am--why are you here?

33:16.342 --> 33:18.039
-What do I want from you?

33:18.083 --> 33:21.347
You know, I believe in choice.

33:23.262 --> 33:25.394
Free choice, okay?

33:25.438 --> 33:28.267
You know what that is, right?
I want you to kill a mouse.

33:30.008 --> 33:32.314
All you gotta do is...

33:32.358 --> 33:35.056
do this,
put his little head in there...

33:35.100 --> 33:36.014
[mousetrap snaps]

33:37.145 --> 33:38.929
It's over. Dead.

33:38.973 --> 33:40.018
-I don't kill animals.

33:40.061 --> 33:41.758
-[laughs]

33:41.802 --> 33:48.026
Did you know
that Hitler was a vegetarian?

33:49.636 --> 33:51.507
It's easy. Trust me.

33:52.682 --> 33:53.901
[mousetrap thuds]

33:53.944 --> 33:55.685
Or...

33:55.729 --> 34:00.212
You know, you could die here
and then he'll eat you.

34:00.255 --> 34:03.084
You want to be eaten by a mouse?

34:03.128 --> 34:04.477
-So why don't you
just kill me right now

34:04.520 --> 34:06.914
and get it over with?

34:06.957 --> 34:09.743
-You really think
I would just kill you, huh?

34:09.786 --> 34:11.223
You're my daughter, Karma.

34:11.266 --> 34:12.833
What kind of a monster
do you think I am?

34:17.707 --> 34:18.969
-I'd rather die.

34:25.324 --> 34:28.196
[mouse squeaking]

34:32.896 --> 34:35.377
[breathing heavily]

34:39.860 --> 34:40.948
[thuds]

34:42.906 --> 34:44.778
[Priscilla panting]

34:54.875 --> 34:55.919
-Hello, rats.

35:01.621 --> 35:03.666
[mouse squeaking]

35:03.710 --> 35:06.539
-[Karma hyperventilating]

35:50.104 --> 35:51.801
[mousetrap snaps]

35:51.845 --> 35:54.717
[tormented squeaking]

35:56.676 --> 35:59.592
[crying]

36:05.554 --> 36:07.077
[gasping]

36:09.602 --> 36:12.431
[suspenseful music]

36:20.830 --> 36:22.049
-Here you go.

36:23.616 --> 36:25.966
Oh! [laughs]

36:26.009 --> 36:28.751
What do you say?

36:28.795 --> 36:30.275
-Please.

36:30.318 --> 36:31.711
-Please what?

36:34.670 --> 36:35.889
-Sir.

36:35.932 --> 36:37.891
-Good job.

36:37.934 --> 36:39.109
Congratulations.

36:40.502 --> 36:41.677
-[drinks aggressively]

36:41.721 --> 36:43.113
-Mm, looky there.

36:44.245 --> 36:46.160
Look what we got here.

36:46.204 --> 36:47.161
[chuckles]

36:49.946 --> 36:54.342
You know, you're all
the same, aren't you?

36:54.386 --> 36:56.475
Just all full of
your own desires.

36:56.518 --> 36:58.172
Slaves to your physical needs.

36:59.913 --> 37:01.219
That's the most
important thing, right?

37:05.832 --> 37:06.963
I should've had a son.

37:31.423 --> 37:32.424
-Wendell!

37:32.467 --> 37:34.774
-[straining]

37:41.128 --> 37:44.044
-Where do you think
you're going?

37:44.087 --> 37:46.307
You can let go of her now.

37:46.351 --> 37:51.181
You know, next time you do that,
you're gonna get shot.

37:51.225 --> 37:52.661
All right?

37:52.705 --> 37:54.097
You can go, Wendell.

37:58.319 --> 38:00.016
What are you so serious about?

38:00.060 --> 38:02.062
You know I'm just
joking around, right?

38:03.846 --> 38:05.326
[laughs]

38:08.895 --> 38:11.463
That shaking thing.
It means I'm getting to you.

38:13.900 --> 38:15.249
It's a really bad habit.

38:17.207 --> 38:22.735
You ever hear of a, uh...
Harry Harlow?

38:22.778 --> 38:24.476
Ring a bell?

38:24.519 --> 38:25.694
No?

38:29.394 --> 38:32.310
And they let you
into Harvard, huh?

38:32.353 --> 38:34.312
[laughs]

38:34.355 --> 38:35.661
You know what he did?

38:36.836 --> 38:39.317
He got a bunch of monkeys,

38:39.360 --> 38:42.015
and he took their mother
away from them.

38:42.058 --> 38:45.235
And then he gave them
a choice of mom:

38:47.499 --> 38:52.895
one made out of wire,
to feed them.

38:52.939 --> 38:58.945
Or a nice, you know,
soft, nice, cozy,

38:58.988 --> 39:02.688
comfortable, gentle mother
to watch them starve.

39:05.212 --> 39:08.215
Which one do you think
they picked, huh?

39:08.258 --> 39:09.608
'Cause I'm trying to find out:

39:09.651 --> 39:11.392
Are you a real girl?

39:11.436 --> 39:13.002
Or a fucking monkey?

39:14.134 --> 39:17.398
Which one are you?

39:17.442 --> 39:19.574
You a fucking monkey?

39:19.618 --> 39:22.838
[imitates monkey noise]

39:22.882 --> 39:25.275
[laughs]

39:25.319 --> 39:27.843
You don't like that, do you?

39:27.887 --> 39:30.498
Which one do you think
they picked, huh?

39:30.542 --> 39:39.246
-Um. [clears throat]
The cold...cold wire mom?

39:39.289 --> 39:40.552
-The wire.

39:40.595 --> 39:42.292
[sucks through his teeth]
Ooh.

39:42.336 --> 39:45.600
No. Of course they picked
the nice, soft, cozy, warm,

39:45.644 --> 39:50.431
comfortable mother
to watch them starve.

39:50.475 --> 39:54.174
Listen...you can leave
if you want.

39:54.217 --> 39:56.742
You can go run away.
It's open.

39:56.785 --> 39:58.091
Go ahead, take it.

40:03.705 --> 40:04.880
Go ahead.

40:07.492 --> 40:08.493
Ooh.

40:09.711 --> 40:11.409
Except for one thing.

40:11.452 --> 40:12.888
Uh, your mom is staying here.

40:15.369 --> 40:18.328
-No. No. I won't leave her.

40:18.372 --> 40:19.417
-Oh yeah, you will.

40:20.592 --> 40:22.202
Yeah, yeah, you are. Yeah.

40:22.245 --> 40:25.858
-No. No. No,
I'm not leaving without my mom.

40:25.901 --> 40:27.294
-You got about five minutes
to make up your mind

40:27.337 --> 40:28.469
because Wendell's
gonna come back out

40:28.513 --> 40:29.775
to check on me, so here.

40:44.529 --> 40:47.357
-Okay. [panting]

40:49.751 --> 40:51.579
[car door closes]

40:51.623 --> 40:53.015
Okay.

40:53.059 --> 40:57.498
[car engine sputters]

40:57.542 --> 41:01.110
Come on. Come on. Come on.
Fucking Sunny.

41:01.154 --> 41:02.982
[car engine sputters]

41:06.942 --> 41:10.511
-Roadside assistance. [laughs]

41:10.555 --> 41:13.079
A little trouble
with your starter there?

41:13.122 --> 41:15.647
That's because I told Wendell
to disengage it,

41:15.690 --> 41:17.344
'cause you ain't going nowhere.

41:22.262 --> 41:23.263
-[gasping]

41:26.701 --> 41:27.702
Mom!

41:34.492 --> 41:36.798
PAUL:
Another weak monkey moment,

41:36.842 --> 41:38.234
ladies and gentlemen.

41:41.194 --> 41:45.154
-Mom? It's me.
Can you talk?

41:47.374 --> 41:49.724
Priscilla! Are you okay?

41:49.768 --> 41:52.422
Do you know where my mom is?

41:52.466 --> 41:54.120
Where's my mom?

41:54.163 --> 41:56.209
[muffled screaming]

42:08.656 --> 42:11.180
-Can I give you
a word of advice?

42:11.224 --> 42:12.442
-Shhh.

42:15.881 --> 42:18.448
-[whispering] I've spent
a lot of time with your father.

42:18.492 --> 42:21.800
And at this point, struggling
can only make things worse.

42:21.843 --> 42:23.845
He wants to break your spirit.

42:23.889 --> 42:25.586
It's not personal.

42:25.630 --> 42:29.982
It's not about violence.
This is just what he does.

42:30.025 --> 42:31.723
He wants to crawl
inside your head

42:31.766 --> 42:34.856
and make you
just as cruel as he is.

42:34.900 --> 42:36.423
-You said no one
was getting in here

42:36.466 --> 42:39.165
unless you let them in.

42:39.208 --> 42:41.297
-I can promise you,
it wasn't me.

42:43.648 --> 42:45.650
I'd rather die than
help that man again.

42:48.609 --> 42:49.828
-Then who was it?

42:58.184 --> 43:01.100
[panting]

43:06.366 --> 43:09.064
-[Wendell whistling the tune
of "Waking Karma"]

43:17.899 --> 43:18.944
[loud thud]

43:18.987 --> 43:21.860
[whistling continues]

43:27.866 --> 43:29.476
-Where's my mom?

43:29.519 --> 43:30.999
-Well, good afternoon
to you, too.

43:33.436 --> 43:36.222
She's right where
she should be, all right?

43:36.265 --> 43:37.440
Ask stupid questions.

43:39.268 --> 43:40.269
-I'm vegan.

43:41.706 --> 43:45.057
-I don't really care
one way or the other.

43:45.100 --> 43:46.275
-I'm not going to eat it.

43:46.319 --> 43:48.016
-Yes, you are.

43:48.060 --> 43:50.149
-Or what?

43:50.192 --> 43:52.107
-Or what?

43:52.151 --> 43:54.240
Well, I tell you, um,

43:56.198 --> 43:58.940
you're never gonna
see your mother again.

43:58.984 --> 44:00.115
How about that?

44:03.162 --> 44:06.426
-So if I eat this,
I can see my mom?

44:06.469 --> 44:08.950
-What's so wonderful
about mothers?

44:10.560 --> 44:12.214
If you tell me what's
so goddamned important

44:12.258 --> 44:14.347
about a mother,
that might help.

44:14.390 --> 44:16.392
-You must have had one.

44:16.436 --> 44:19.918
-Your grandma
was a real peach of a woman.

44:19.961 --> 44:22.660
The--the fucking face
that launched a thousand drunks.

44:22.703 --> 44:24.487
-Paul. Spare the girl.

44:26.011 --> 44:27.708
PAUL: Why?

44:27.752 --> 44:30.058
What's so goddamned important
about being a mother?

44:30.102 --> 44:35.281
I was thinking maybe we should
ask, uh, Priscilla.

44:35.324 --> 44:36.891
She's a mom. She would know.

44:36.935 --> 44:38.676
Maybe she has some insight.

44:38.719 --> 44:40.199
-You know she doesn't speak.

44:40.242 --> 44:42.680
Please.

44:42.723 --> 44:44.725
-Yeah, well.

44:44.769 --> 44:46.640
Not many marriages can survive,

44:46.684 --> 44:51.601
you know, a daughter's throat
being slit by the father.

44:51.645 --> 44:52.951
Right, Butch?

44:55.301 --> 44:56.824
[laughs]
-[Priscilla cries]

44:56.868 --> 44:58.347
-I mean,
you don't even know

44:58.391 --> 44:59.827
what happened
between these two, do you?

44:59.871 --> 45:01.263
-They told me
you killed their daughter.

45:01.307 --> 45:03.352
-[laughs]
Oh, that's a good one.

45:05.833 --> 45:07.922
-I never said
he was the one who did it.

45:09.489 --> 45:11.230
-All right...so.

45:15.625 --> 45:19.281
[laughing]
The mute's crying now! Yes.

45:19.325 --> 45:21.544
-Paul, I deserve this,
all right?

45:21.588 --> 45:22.937
Every second of it.

45:22.981 --> 45:25.157
But these two
haven't done anything.

45:25.200 --> 45:27.115
Let them go.

45:27.159 --> 45:29.683
Let them go! Do whatever
you want with me.

45:29.727 --> 45:31.424
-You--you really mean that?

45:31.467 --> 45:32.599
-Yes.

45:32.642 --> 45:33.774
PAUL: Well, all right.

45:33.818 --> 45:35.167
-Argh!

45:35.210 --> 45:37.082
God!

45:37.125 --> 45:39.214
-[gasps]
-I decide what you deserve.

45:39.258 --> 45:40.955
-[grunts]

45:40.999 --> 45:43.610
-Eat your food.
Or I won't take the knife out.

45:43.653 --> 45:44.916
-[through gritted teeth] Karma,
you don't have to do

45:44.959 --> 45:46.265
anything you don't want to.

45:46.308 --> 45:47.788
You don't have to.

45:47.832 --> 45:51.226
-Eat your food.
-[Butch grunting]

45:51.270 --> 45:54.882
-Eat your meat.
Eat it.

45:54.926 --> 45:56.797
Eat it all!

45:56.841 --> 45:59.017
-[Butch grunts]

45:59.060 --> 46:01.193
-That's a good girl.

46:01.236 --> 46:02.237
BUTCH: Ah!

46:04.457 --> 46:06.502
[Priscilla cries]

46:11.203 --> 46:12.813
-Now you're worse than me.

46:12.857 --> 46:14.336
-Worse than you?

46:14.380 --> 46:16.208
-[laughs]

46:20.212 --> 46:24.216
You know, I was your age
when I killed my mother.

46:25.695 --> 46:28.046
She was the first one.

46:28.089 --> 46:30.788
Yeah. But at least
I didn't eat her.

46:30.831 --> 46:33.225
-Where's my mom?

46:33.268 --> 46:35.923
-Well. There she is,
right there.

46:35.967 --> 46:37.795
BUTCH: Oh, Jesus.

46:47.674 --> 46:52.374
-[coughs, gags, vomits]

46:52.418 --> 46:53.767
PAUL: Well, I promised you
if you ate,

46:53.811 --> 46:55.290
you'd see her again.

46:56.857 --> 46:59.338
Wendell. Get rid of these two.

46:59.381 --> 47:02.254
-[Karma coughing]

47:19.010 --> 47:23.231
[crying] Mom.

47:25.407 --> 47:27.496
-You're a very good girl.

47:27.540 --> 47:31.457
-[sobbing]

47:43.730 --> 47:46.907
[♪♪♪]

47:56.264 --> 47:57.483
WENDELL: Stay here.

48:04.272 --> 48:05.534
Come on. Stand up.

48:07.232 --> 48:08.450
Here.

48:14.892 --> 48:17.895
-[laughing]

48:19.418 --> 48:27.556
[clears throat] You know, um...
I'm very proud of you.

48:28.906 --> 48:30.908
What you did at lunchtime.

48:32.170 --> 48:36.130
You earned the right of choice.

48:36.174 --> 48:37.262
These two?

48:39.699 --> 48:43.529
I'll fucking kill them both
right now.

48:43.572 --> 48:45.096
I'll stab them to death.

48:47.707 --> 48:49.927
But you earned the right
to decide.

48:53.017 --> 48:57.499
You kill one of them
or I'll do them both.

49:01.199 --> 49:02.896
-Karma.

49:02.940 --> 49:04.898
Karma, I'm begging you.

49:04.942 --> 49:06.900
Kill me, leave Priscilla.

49:06.944 --> 49:08.380
Let Priscilla live.

49:08.423 --> 49:09.903
Baby...

49:13.646 --> 49:15.169
please.

49:15.213 --> 49:16.692
-Come on.

49:20.827 --> 49:22.133
Good girl.

49:24.004 --> 49:26.311
You could actually save a life.

49:29.096 --> 49:30.968
BUTCH: Kill me!

49:31.011 --> 49:32.360
Please, Karma.

49:33.622 --> 49:34.972
-Do it!

49:37.235 --> 49:39.063
The time is now.

49:40.412 --> 49:42.980
Butch or Priscilla, which one?
Who you gonna do?

49:45.417 --> 49:47.201
-Let them both go.

49:51.292 --> 49:55.035
-[Paul laughs]

49:55.079 --> 49:58.038
You're gonna stab yourself,
is that it?

49:58.082 --> 50:00.084
Yeah, you know how hard
that is to do?

50:02.912 --> 50:05.393
You're not even going to get
through your T-shirt, all right?

50:21.844 --> 50:22.889
[switchblade clicks]

50:24.195 --> 50:29.069
Let's give Butch
a really good show.

50:29.113 --> 50:30.244
What do you think?

50:32.116 --> 50:33.595
Huh? All right.

50:33.639 --> 50:37.860
-No!! No.

50:42.691 --> 50:44.041
-[agonal cough]

50:45.390 --> 50:46.913
[Paul laughs]

50:52.440 --> 50:55.052
[Butch sobbing]

51:09.283 --> 51:10.197
PAUL: You know,

51:11.894 --> 51:16.943
when I was a kid, I really
didn't get fed enough.

51:18.858 --> 51:22.949
My mother didn't really
feed me good.

51:22.992 --> 51:25.517
So, one day I took a stick.

51:25.560 --> 51:30.739
I was so fucking hungry that

51:30.783 --> 51:32.872
I killed a rat.

51:32.915 --> 51:36.267
With a stick. And I ate it.

51:36.310 --> 51:38.660
That's how, you know,
hungry I was.

51:38.704 --> 51:41.141
See, and there's a rat,
right there.

51:43.448 --> 51:46.799
You know what it's like to
have a rat in your life?

51:46.842 --> 51:49.845
You know, who wants that? Right?

51:49.889 --> 51:51.804
That's not good for Papa.
Is it?

51:53.240 --> 51:55.721
A rat, on a stick.

51:55.764 --> 51:57.636
Open up your mouth, rat.

51:57.679 --> 51:59.290
Open up!

52:00.943 --> 52:02.336
-Fuck you.

52:04.295 --> 52:06.688
-[groans] Mom?

52:06.732 --> 52:08.603
Mom?
-PAUL: Open up your mouth!

52:08.647 --> 52:10.039
-I thought you were dead.

52:10.083 --> 52:12.825
He told me that you...
Are you okay?

52:12.868 --> 52:15.436
Where were you? Mom!

52:18.874 --> 52:21.355
-[Butch gurgles]
-[Karma gasping]

52:21.399 --> 52:22.878
Mom!

52:25.577 --> 52:27.448
Mom!

52:27.492 --> 52:30.190
What's going on? What?
Is he making you do this?

52:30.234 --> 52:32.453
-Nothing.
No, no, of course not.

52:32.497 --> 52:33.715
-So you just decided
to come out

52:33.759 --> 52:35.587
and save his life
instead of mine?

52:35.630 --> 52:38.851
-I believe in
the power of choice, honey.

52:38.894 --> 52:41.506
-That's something he thinks;
that's not something you think.

52:41.549 --> 52:43.421
-We think the same things.

52:43.464 --> 52:45.423
-Since when?!

52:45.466 --> 52:47.207
-Let's talk
about this later, okay?

52:47.251 --> 52:51.037
You're tired and you don't know
what you're saying.

52:51.080 --> 52:53.692
-I thought we were
best friends, Mom.

52:53.735 --> 52:56.042
-Of course we are.

52:56.085 --> 52:59.828
But this is the highest honor
I could hope for for you, Karma.

52:59.872 --> 53:01.221
-What are you talking about?

53:01.265 --> 53:04.181
How--how is this an honor?

53:04.224 --> 53:06.183
Did he drug you? Mom?

53:09.882 --> 53:13.102
-Hey, listen.
You know what?

53:13.146 --> 53:17.281
This woman right here
has never wavered against me,

53:17.324 --> 53:22.590
never went away from me,
for 17 years.

53:22.634 --> 53:24.897
You know, she gave birth to you,
you know,

53:24.940 --> 53:26.115
to save her own skin,

53:26.159 --> 53:29.075
but nevertheless,
she did do that.

53:33.688 --> 53:36.256
-The path is clear, Karma.

53:38.302 --> 53:39.955
The soul may reject the vessel,

53:39.999 --> 53:42.523
but not if she's
a perfect genetic match.

53:45.874 --> 53:47.136
A daughter.

53:51.402 --> 53:53.665
-You bred me for him?

53:57.321 --> 53:59.888
[spits]

53:59.932 --> 54:03.240
You fucking bitch.
You don't deserve to live!

54:03.283 --> 54:04.937
[slap thrown]

54:08.027 --> 54:11.204
-PAUL: Wendell!
-[cries] Ah! Ah!

54:11.248 --> 54:13.728
No! No! No!

54:13.772 --> 54:16.383
Mom, please.

54:16.427 --> 54:19.430
Mom. Mom!

54:20.866 --> 54:24.348
-Honey,
we have great news for you.

54:24.391 --> 54:26.741
Should I tell her,
or do you want to?

54:26.785 --> 54:29.744
-Uh, you go ahead.

54:29.788 --> 54:33.313
-You passed. Yay!

54:33.357 --> 54:35.228
It was touch and go there
for a while

54:35.272 --> 54:37.709
with your attachment to me,
but you came through at the end

54:37.752 --> 54:41.147
and you really
stuck the landing.

54:41.190 --> 54:43.410
-Yeah, you sure did.

54:43.454 --> 54:44.803
I'm proud of you, Karma.

54:44.846 --> 54:46.892
-Fuck you,
you fucking psychopath.

54:46.935 --> 54:49.677
-You see?
I told you she had spirit.

54:49.721 --> 54:52.985
-Well, I mean,
you were right,

54:53.028 --> 54:56.380
but she also had
a lot of bad habits,

54:56.423 --> 55:00.775
and sometimes you have to
break somebody's spirit

55:00.819 --> 55:04.475
to get rid of bad habits,
and that's what we did, so...

55:08.696 --> 55:10.219
-So can I leave now?

55:10.263 --> 55:12.047
-Even better.

55:12.091 --> 55:13.527
You might not like
the sound of this at first,

55:13.571 --> 55:15.921
but I promise you,
it's going to be amazing.

55:17.879 --> 55:21.883
-Karma, you and I
are going to spend

55:21.927 --> 55:26.279
the rest of our lives together,
starting tonight.

55:29.108 --> 55:30.457
-What?

55:30.501 --> 55:32.720
-I mean,
there's really no higher honor.

55:32.764 --> 55:34.374
I would have offered
to do it myself,

55:34.418 --> 55:37.246
but I wouldn't be
a genetic match.

55:39.727 --> 55:41.250
-But I thought
if I survived then...

55:41.294 --> 55:43.078
-Oh, no, no.
This was never about survival.

55:43.122 --> 55:46.168
It was about getting you ready.

55:46.212 --> 55:48.693
-Ready for what?

55:48.736 --> 55:52.827
-You have to break
the spirit of the host

55:52.871 --> 55:59.094
before the new soul
enters the body.

55:59.138 --> 56:02.097
-And in your case, honey,
we had to prepare you

56:02.141 --> 56:06.798
for a level of brutality
that you were used to rejecting

56:06.841 --> 56:08.756
so you could match up
with your dad.

56:11.368 --> 56:16.111
-Mom. This makes no sense.
Please tell me you hear that.

56:16.155 --> 56:21.726
-I know it's unfamiliar. But
it's the simplest thing.

56:21.769 --> 56:23.902
You're going to be the host

56:23.945 --> 56:26.600
for the soul
of the greatest prophet

56:26.644 --> 56:29.864
the world has ever known:
your father.

56:32.867 --> 56:34.565
Congratulations.

56:39.613 --> 56:42.399
-PAUL: Wendell!
-No, no, no, no, no, no!

56:44.923 --> 56:46.490
Let me go! Let me go!

56:46.533 --> 56:49.188
[breathing heavily]

56:49.231 --> 56:52.321
Mom? Mom? Mom? Mom?

56:52.365 --> 56:53.932
-Let's get you
cleaned up, okay?

56:53.975 --> 56:56.021
Everything will
look brighter then.

56:57.631 --> 57:01.113
Shhhh.

57:01.156 --> 57:04.377
Good girl, baby girl.
Good girl.

57:04.421 --> 57:05.378
-[breathing heavily]

57:11.515 --> 57:14.779
[breathes deeply]

57:29.663 --> 57:32.797
-Oh, good. You're awake.

57:32.840 --> 57:36.583
We have a ton to get through
before nightfall.

57:36.627 --> 57:38.933
-Mom, what are you doing?
What--what's going on?

57:38.977 --> 57:41.109
-My first question
for you is,

57:41.153 --> 57:43.634
are you on your period?

57:43.677 --> 57:46.245
-Why? What is this for?

57:46.288 --> 57:47.464
-Are you menstruating,
yes or no?

57:47.507 --> 57:50.118
We need to be quick here.

57:50.162 --> 57:51.729
-No.
No, don't you remember

57:51.772 --> 57:54.775
when I took your last tampon
two weeks ago?

57:54.819 --> 57:58.431
-I do. But these are
for your father.

57:58.475 --> 58:00.825
-Why does he need to know
if I'm having my period?

58:03.915 --> 58:05.525
-I'd appreciate
if you would pee in here

58:05.569 --> 58:08.702
and let me see the toilet paper,
just to be sure.

58:12.314 --> 58:13.838
-Absolutely not.

58:16.971 --> 58:18.625
-I know this all
seems strange but, believe me,

58:18.669 --> 58:20.758
it's in your own best interest
to cooperate.

58:27.025 --> 58:30.507
-If I pee for you, will
you answer a question for me?

58:30.550 --> 58:32.291
As my mom?

58:32.334 --> 58:33.814
-Fine.

58:46.827 --> 58:50.396
-[peeing]

59:00.493 --> 59:02.016
-You're clean.

59:07.021 --> 59:08.675
-Mom?

59:08.719 --> 59:10.068
What did he have to do to you

59:10.111 --> 59:12.461
to convince
you to do this to me?

59:12.505 --> 59:13.898
-Nothing.

59:15.377 --> 59:18.337
I'd do anything for him.

59:18.380 --> 59:21.166
And it's not "to" you.
It's for you.

59:22.646 --> 59:25.562
-You wouldn't do
anything for me?

59:25.605 --> 59:28.695
-It's different.

59:28.739 --> 59:30.218
Is it possible
that you're not menstruating

59:30.262 --> 59:32.699
because you're pregnant?

59:32.743 --> 59:34.396
-I'm sorry?

59:34.440 --> 59:36.050
-Just answer the question.

59:36.094 --> 59:38.183
-Mom, you know
the answer to that.

59:38.226 --> 59:39.663
-I need to
hear you to say it.

59:41.099 --> 59:42.622
-No.

59:42.666 --> 59:46.191
It's not possible
I'm pregnant.

59:46.234 --> 59:47.235
[sniffles]

59:47.279 --> 59:48.628
-Are you a virgin?

59:51.500 --> 59:54.068
-Where were you for the
last three years of high school

59:54.112 --> 59:55.722
while I cried to you
that I couldn't get a date

59:55.766 --> 59:58.029
because everyone thought
I was weird?

1:00:00.640 --> 1:00:02.511
-I'll take that as a yes.

1:00:02.555 --> 1:00:04.818
Are you a lesbian?

1:00:04.862 --> 1:00:06.080
-What does it matter?

1:00:06.124 --> 1:00:07.473
-Yes or no?

1:00:10.084 --> 1:00:14.611
-No. I like boys,
they just don't like me.

1:00:18.876 --> 1:00:22.183
-I'll need you to submit
to a virginity test.

1:00:24.098 --> 1:00:26.927
-Are you--
are you fucking kidding me?

1:00:26.971 --> 1:00:31.192
Mom, you know
those tests are bullshit.

1:00:31.236 --> 1:00:33.542
-Your father requires it.

1:00:42.987 --> 1:00:44.858
-[sniffles]

1:00:56.174 --> 1:00:58.698
-Wendell,
would you come in here, please?

1:00:58.742 --> 1:01:00.352
I need your help with something.

1:01:02.354 --> 1:01:04.965
KARMA: No, no, no, no.

1:01:05.009 --> 1:01:07.011
Mom, no! No, Mom!

1:01:07.054 --> 1:01:10.362
No! You can't do this.

1:01:10.405 --> 1:01:12.538
Mom, this isn't you.

1:01:12.581 --> 1:01:15.367
No! No!

1:01:15.410 --> 1:01:17.891
-That plush monkey
you grew up with,

1:01:17.935 --> 1:01:23.070
who you thought you knew?
That wasn't me.

1:01:23.114 --> 1:01:24.942
I told her to you
as a bedtime story

1:01:24.985 --> 1:01:27.248
so you could fall asleep
at night.

1:01:27.292 --> 1:01:28.815
-No.

1:01:28.859 --> 1:01:31.818
-But now it's time
to wake up and grow up.

1:01:31.862 --> 1:01:32.993
-[crying] Please.

1:01:33.037 --> 1:01:35.953
-This is the real me,

1:01:35.996 --> 1:01:37.737
whether you like her or not.

1:01:41.219 --> 1:01:42.437
[flashlight clicks]

1:01:42.481 --> 1:01:44.962
-[cries]

1:01:51.664 --> 1:01:53.187
-Everything looks good.

1:01:55.276 --> 1:01:56.713
We'll give you a second.

1:02:02.588 --> 1:02:05.896
[footsteps]

1:02:16.602 --> 1:02:19.692
-[breathing shakily]

1:02:22.390 --> 1:02:26.525
[footsteps]

1:02:26.568 --> 1:02:28.788
-Get up.
You've had long enough.

1:02:32.531 --> 1:02:34.228
-[cattle prod crackles]
-[groans]

1:02:34.272 --> 1:02:35.447
SUNNY: I said, get up.

1:02:37.797 --> 1:02:40.800
-[cries]

1:02:46.414 --> 1:02:47.633
-Put these on.

1:02:49.113 --> 1:02:50.157
-No.

1:02:51.855 --> 1:02:53.117
-Suit yourself.

1:02:54.335 --> 1:02:55.554
[shoes thud]

1:02:59.645 --> 1:03:00.951
-[sniffles]

1:03:03.388 --> 1:03:06.434
-I need you to dig. Here.

1:03:07.653 --> 1:03:09.002
-How deep?

1:03:09.046 --> 1:03:10.656
-At least six feet.

1:03:10.699 --> 1:03:13.267
-So it's a grave.

1:03:13.311 --> 1:03:16.270
-Get digging.
The sun will be going down soon.

1:03:19.360 --> 1:03:22.233
-[sniffles] Is it for me?

1:03:22.276 --> 1:03:25.540
-That depends entirely
on how the ritual goes.

1:03:25.584 --> 1:03:27.978
-So, if it fails...

1:03:28.021 --> 1:03:29.544
-If the soul
rejects the vessel,

1:03:29.588 --> 1:03:31.851
then the vessel is corrupt,
and we must...

1:03:31.895 --> 1:03:33.374
we must dispose of it.

1:03:35.899 --> 1:03:37.378
-And what happens to you?

1:03:39.511 --> 1:03:40.817
-All I know is that
if you don't do

1:03:40.860 --> 1:03:42.688
exactly what I say
and do it now,

1:03:42.731 --> 1:03:43.863
I'm going to lose both you

1:03:43.907 --> 1:03:45.343
and your father in one night.

1:03:48.520 --> 1:03:53.133
-Mom, have any of
these rituals ever worked?

1:03:53.177 --> 1:03:55.919
-This one is different.

1:03:55.962 --> 1:03:59.531
His power,
your genetic match,

1:03:59.574 --> 1:04:04.231
the presence of the divine,
everything we've sacrificed.

1:04:04.275 --> 1:04:07.060
This one will work
if you do what I say.

1:04:07.104 --> 1:04:09.758
-So you're saying
they've all failed?

1:04:13.023 --> 1:04:15.764
Mom. Mom,

1:04:15.808 --> 1:04:18.680
let's get out of here together
right now, okay?

1:04:18.724 --> 1:04:20.552
Then I don't have to die,

1:04:20.595 --> 1:04:23.076
and neither does that fucking
monster you think you love.

1:04:24.686 --> 1:04:27.254
-[cattle prod crackles]
-[gasps]

1:04:27.298 --> 1:04:30.823
-You don't know him.
Now start shoveling.

1:04:41.007 --> 1:04:45.446
Physical exhaustion
will purify the vessel.

1:04:57.154 --> 1:04:59.112
Shallow.

1:04:59.156 --> 1:05:00.722
But it'll have to do.

1:05:02.115 --> 1:05:05.031
-[panting]

1:05:07.816 --> 1:05:11.559
Mom, I'm starving.

1:05:13.474 --> 1:05:17.043
-Hunger will purify
the vessel.

1:05:20.960 --> 1:05:23.963
[water running in sink]

1:05:24.007 --> 1:05:27.097
[soft music playing]

1:06:38.951 --> 1:06:41.475
-I don't understand
how you pretended.

1:06:41.519 --> 1:06:44.478
With me.

1:06:44.522 --> 1:06:46.437
-I was never pretending.

1:06:48.439 --> 1:06:52.356
-Did you meet him?
Behind my back?

1:06:52.399 --> 1:06:56.316
-Never.
He told me to wait.

1:06:59.493 --> 1:07:01.974
-And you waited.

1:07:02.018 --> 1:07:03.541
-I waited.

1:07:07.675 --> 1:07:10.026
-You thought
about him, though.

1:07:10.069 --> 1:07:11.723
And never told me.

1:07:21.428 --> 1:07:23.474
He doesn't love you.

1:07:28.566 --> 1:07:30.220
-It doesn't matter.

1:07:30.263 --> 1:07:31.656
-But I do.

1:07:40.882 --> 1:07:43.233
-He gave me
everything I have.

1:07:46.714 --> 1:07:48.629
But you?

1:07:48.673 --> 1:07:53.112
You took and you took,

1:07:53.156 --> 1:07:56.724
and you never
gave any of it back.

1:07:59.118 --> 1:08:00.598
-Are you kidding?

1:08:01.860 --> 1:08:03.340
All I ever did
was take care of you.

1:08:03.383 --> 1:08:05.429
You were never a real mom.

1:08:08.475 --> 1:08:10.173
[groans]

1:08:10.216 --> 1:08:13.001
[water splashing]

1:08:16.614 --> 1:08:20.052
-[straining]

1:08:20.096 --> 1:08:22.707
Aaaahhh! [cries]

1:08:31.498 --> 1:08:34.022
-[coughing,
breathing rapidly]

1:08:51.127 --> 1:08:52.432
-I wanted to do that
a hundred times

1:08:52.476 --> 1:08:54.130
when you were a baby.

1:08:55.696 --> 1:08:57.045
I couldn't go through with it

1:08:57.089 --> 1:08:58.221
because I knew
Paul would kill me.

1:09:02.964 --> 1:09:04.966
You stole my life.

1:09:08.100 --> 1:09:09.841
I never wanted you.

1:09:13.061 --> 1:09:16.152
I only had you because
your father told me to.

1:09:20.286 --> 1:09:22.462
Is that what
you wanted to hear, Karma?

1:09:25.248 --> 1:09:27.685
Because that's the truth.

1:09:27.728 --> 1:09:31.036
-[breathing heavily, crying]

1:09:33.517 --> 1:09:37.347
-[breathes]

1:09:42.221 --> 1:09:45.746
Wendell! We're done here.

1:09:45.790 --> 1:09:49.185
[Karma sobbing]

1:10:12.686 --> 1:10:14.558
-You want her someplace else?

1:10:14.601 --> 1:10:16.603
-No, thank you.

1:10:16.647 --> 1:10:18.257
Could you give us
some privacy, though?

1:10:23.610 --> 1:10:25.351
I have a present for you.

1:10:39.496 --> 1:10:42.455
Your father and I
would like you to wear this.

1:10:45.980 --> 1:10:47.504
And then you can put the mask on

1:10:47.547 --> 1:10:49.332
and go out to the yard
and we'll meet you there.

1:10:58.123 --> 1:11:02.258
You know, after everything
he's done for you today,

1:11:04.260 --> 1:11:07.045
I think you could stand
to lose the attitude.

1:11:07.088 --> 1:11:10.309
You're lucky to have a father
who wanted you.

1:11:10.353 --> 1:11:12.093
Not everyone does, you know.

1:11:13.617 --> 1:11:16.794
And sometimes
we have to sacrifice.

1:11:16.837 --> 1:11:21.364
You think it was easy for me to
raise you alone with no money?

1:11:21.407 --> 1:11:22.756
I can tell you
I didn't get it done

1:11:22.800 --> 1:11:24.149
by sitting around
and crying about it.

1:11:29.197 --> 1:11:31.896
And sometimes we have to--

1:11:31.939 --> 1:11:35.943
buck up and play the hand
that fate dealt us.

1:11:40.208 --> 1:11:43.342
So even if you don't like it,

1:11:43.386 --> 1:11:46.040
you'll put on the dress
when I tell you to.

1:11:46.084 --> 1:11:47.564
Because I am your mother.

1:11:51.959 --> 1:11:53.221
-No, you're not.

1:11:56.486 --> 1:11:58.096
You never were.

1:12:00.881 --> 1:12:03.014
[slap thrown]

1:12:03.057 --> 1:12:06.800
[crying]

1:12:06.844 --> 1:12:07.714
SUNNY: Fine.

1:12:10.413 --> 1:12:12.545
Then do it so your father
doesn't gut you like a fish.

1:12:12.589 --> 1:12:15.331
Is that enough motivation
for you?

1:12:27.212 --> 1:12:30.433
-[breathing heavily]

1:12:36.874 --> 1:12:39.616
[crying]

1:12:47.058 --> 1:12:48.233
[sniffles]

1:12:49.887 --> 1:12:52.498
[emotional music playing]

1:12:56.894 --> 1:12:58.199
[sniffling]

1:13:50.687 --> 1:13:53.559
[breathing
through the mask]

1:14:14.014 --> 1:14:15.581
PAUL: Thank you, Wendell.

1:14:15.625 --> 1:14:18.454
[Wendell whistling the tune
of "Waking Karma"]

1:14:52.444 --> 1:14:55.491
[intense music playing]

1:15:02.759 --> 1:15:04.064
PAUL: Hello, Karma.

1:15:06.806 --> 1:15:08.025
You know,

1:15:09.592 --> 1:15:11.202
I've been a fucking monster.

1:15:16.294 --> 1:15:18.252
You know, it ain't no fun
being an animal.

1:15:18.296 --> 1:15:21.212
It gets to the point where
it just ain't fun no more...

1:15:22.343 --> 1:15:24.345
[screams in pain]

1:15:24.389 --> 1:15:27.435
[blood splattering]

1:15:35.618 --> 1:15:38.534
-[breathing
through the mask]

1:15:48.631 --> 1:15:51.503
[suspenseful music playing]

1:17:05.533 --> 1:17:06.665
[razor thuds]

1:17:15.500 --> 1:17:16.806
SUNNY: Paul?

1:17:16.849 --> 1:17:20.461
[breathes heavily]

1:17:20.505 --> 1:17:21.898
It's really you.

1:17:29.645 --> 1:17:31.168
[cries in happiness]
Wendell.

1:17:32.691 --> 1:17:34.780
The soul has accepted
the vessel.

1:17:36.652 --> 1:17:38.131
The vessel is holy.

1:17:41.569 --> 1:17:43.528
You'll need to bury
the discarded shell.

1:17:43.571 --> 1:17:45.182
I believe it's still
in the bathroom.

1:18:01.764 --> 1:18:04.636
[trash bag rustles]

1:18:08.901 --> 1:18:12.122
-[exhales]

1:18:13.210 --> 1:18:14.515
[strains]

1:18:16.387 --> 1:18:19.390
-Oh, God, there's so much I want
to ask you.

1:18:19.433 --> 1:18:21.958
What did it feel like?

1:18:22.001 --> 1:18:24.177
Did you touch divinity
on the other side?

1:18:27.659 --> 1:18:29.052
You must be tired.

1:18:31.402 --> 1:18:33.926
But we have plenty of time
to catch up now.

1:18:35.449 --> 1:18:37.321
Years and years...

1:18:50.247 --> 1:18:52.597
Have I told you
how much I missed you?

1:18:55.034 --> 1:18:57.297
All those lonely nights...

1:18:57.341 --> 1:19:00.257
[Karma breathing through the
mask]

1:19:08.656 --> 1:19:09.962
-What are you doing?

1:19:16.926 --> 1:19:18.797
Wendell!

1:19:18.841 --> 1:19:23.019
Get out here right away!
The vessel is corrupt.

1:19:24.150 --> 1:19:26.283
-No!

1:19:26.326 --> 1:19:28.981
-We were wrong.
The vessel is corrupt.

1:19:29.025 --> 1:19:30.069
[Karma cries]

1:19:30.113 --> 1:19:31.244
-I saw him in her.

1:19:31.288 --> 1:19:33.420
